##Ferrymen on the streets of Wuhan: Processing 1,000 messages a minute, not afraid of infection, how to get to work without medical staff | in-depth report

Wechat Bqshenyidu

Features, Beijing Youth Daily, the official public number

Reporter / Leung Ting Intern Reporter / Lee yat-ming Chan wai-king

Editor / Shi Aihua, Liu Mi

Volunteer drivers take selfies with medical staff

Since January 23, several notices from Wuhan's new pneumonia command have cut off public transport in and around the city. Has closed the airport, the railway station from the Han Channel. After the city's bus, subway, ferry and long-distance passenger transport has been suspended, the city has also suspended the network to hire taxis, which are limited to even and odd numbers.

After the shutdown, 6,000 taxis were dispatched to communities in Wuhan's central district to serve residents and medical staff. Deep once reporters learned that although each community equipped with 3 to 5 taxis, but still exists in the community medical staff commuting to and from work. A non-biker nurse in Hankou has to get up at 5 am and walk nearly three hours a day to get to work.

At one point, a reporter called several communities in Wuhan and received mixed responses to the question of whether vehicles could transport medical staff. Some staff said the community taxi for the use of the elderly and young patients, medical staff have a separate car. Staff also mentioned that taxis can be used when there is spare time, there is no spare medical staff to find their own way.

On the day of the Wuhan Public Transport Closure, a number of civilian volunteer convoys were set up at the same time, some organized by individuals, some sponsored by trade associations, and volunteers volunteered to pick up and deliver medical personnel and supplies.

Since the exit route from Wuhan was closed, while the volunteer drivers had to do their part to support Wuhan, they also had to face unexpected accidents and risks of illness. Among the volunteers, some people need to carry their families "secretly" out to help, some drivers every day to receive hundreds of phone calls, more than a dozen compulsory pick-up and drop-off, working 22 hours. Some volunteer drivers have a fever, some have had a car accident, and some have left the service because they can not bear the pressure from their families.

Because the volunteer motorcade is not professional enough, the sponsor once considered stopping the volunteer motorcade, but because many medical workers rely on the volunteer motorcade, "stopping" is actually difficult to do. Currently, thousands of private motorcade owners have joined the volunteer motorcade, back and forth between the community and the hospital, Wuhan as a special period of folk "ferryman. ".

Warm blood

The alarm went off at 6:20 a.m. , but Tsuneyasu didn't hear it, and it was 6:50. The nurse was supposed to be at the Mental Health Center at 7:00, and she was in a bit of a hurry. He grabbed his phone, sent a message to the nurse, changed his clothes, and went out without washing.

She tiptoes, dare not make a sound, because this "action" is hidden from parents.

On the morning of the New Year's Day, it was dark. It was raining in Wuhan. There were few cars along the road. It was the first time Tsuneyasu had volunteered to help transport medical staff. "I've been thinking about driving faster and not making people late. "

Tsuneyasu, 22, is a local college student in Wuhan. New Year's Eve was having lunch, she brush friends circle, see because the medical staff travel difficulties, civilian is organizing a car. She tried to join in, and after two back and forth arguments with her parents, she failed. Parents adamantly opposed, "they finally threw out a direct line, not you strong head time, if you are ill we do? This I stuffed to death, have no words. "

Parental anxiety is realistic -- it's dangerous outside of Florida, and health care workers are at high risk. The city's Health Commission had previously reported 15 confirmed cases of pneumonia and one suspected case of COVID-19 in the city.

But Tsuneyasu managed to sneak into the group, which already had more than 400 volunteer drivers and paramedics, and people were constantly texting for help. She also found in the Group of Guitar Teacher, they briefly exchange: "You also into the Group, Worthy of my admiration of the master" , "well done, worthy of my apprentice.

7:20, they meet up. Tsuneyasu heard from a nurse that her colleague, who lives in Hankou and can not ride a bicycle, had to walk for three hours to get to the hospital after 5 a.m. The nurse kept thanking Tsuneyasu, "there's no taxi now, not you, I don't know how to get to work. " That night, the nurse also posted a friend's message, "thank you for getting up in the dark in the morning and taking me to work. I don't know you, but thank you from the bottom of my heart. "

In Wuhan, thousands of people, like Tsuneyasu, have joined the volunteer convoy. They often see messages asking for help in their friend circles. They need to transport supplies such as masks and protective clothing. They also need to transport medical personnel. They scan codes to join different groups, the simplest goodness in human nature is revealed little by little.

A 12-year-old veteran of the Wenchuan County earthquake relief effort, Xiang, took his car to the streets of Wuhan, where his motto is "no hurry, no stop" . In addition to picking up and dropping off medical staff, he also occasionally picks up patients' families.

A mother in the volunteer group to see the need to pick up, for their junior son signed up. She wants her son to have a sense of responsibility, to meet more people and to know the society. The mother had a similar episode in mid-october, with fever, diarrhea, and pain until late November. She is not overly concerned about the outbreak.

But the panic was not so easily defused, as two elderly members of the family objected, and one boy quit on New Year's Eve after joining the volunteer motorcade. His home near the South China Wholesale Seafood Market, parents over 60, colleagues of the family infection, two old very worried. He had to give up and choose to do vehicle dispatch service.

After dropping off the nurse in the morning, Tsuneyasu hurried home. It's not 9:00, and her parents are still asleep, so she's covered. Because he's young, Tsuneyasu says, there's a lot of blood in his veins, and he's excited and scared when he drives out. At this particular time, she finally helped someone. But also a bit embarrassed, the nurse gets off a car, she can Meng spray disinfection water, "although I a cavity hot blood, but still afraid. "

Volunteers transfer relief supplies

Bring together

Most volunteer motorcades are set up on New Year's Eve.

On January 23, the Wuhan new pneumonia prevention and Control Headquarters issued five notices in succession. Have closed the airport, railway station from the Han Channel. In the city bus, subway, ferry and long-distance passenger transport after the suspension of the network about the taxi, the implementation of parade Taxi odd-even Number Limit.

Public transport was shut down, and travel became a problem first. On the morning of January 24, Pingkang's circle of friends had medical friends asking for help: Many colleagues walked to work, and pregnant women who were eight months pregnant also rode bicycles to work. Ping Kang replied, "I want to help you. ".

He took a screenshot of himself asking for help in his circle of friends and then entered the wechat group for medical travel support. At first, he was just trying to help a friend. After entering the group, saw too many people want a car, began to help the main group together to find a driver. Pingkang introduction, the then group leader is not Wuhan People, Unfamiliar With the Wuhan Road, Pingkang became the new administrator. That day opened four groups, the first two groups soon full, Pingkang and pulled a group of more responsible friends to join together, began to operate.

Some teams are formed in a completely passive way. He couldn't laugh or cry at the idea of becoming the leader of the group. He read an online recruitment message from the Wuhan Red Cross and forwarded it. I was only going to be a volunteer, but a big V retweeted it and took his micro signal with him. From two o'clock in the afternoon of New Year's Eve, one or two hundred people started to add him within an hour. He had no choice but to be the owner of the group

In addition to travel, large-scale material distribution is also affected. Shi Jun, Secretary General of the Wuhan Logistics Association, told Shenyidai that before January 23, they were piecemeal linking up the work of non-provincial logistics in the city of Wuhan to deliver goods. After the Lunar New Year's Eve, many drivers in Wuhan have already returned home for the construction of the Huoshenshan Hospital. We're short-handed. No one's delivering the trailer or the container. After reporting to the Public Security Bureau, Traffic Bureau and other departments, they issued an initiative to drivers in Han.

At present they have two groups, one is the delivery of large goods truck group, has 213 people. The other is a group of private cars carrying small supplies, also more than 200 people. But neither the number of drivers nor the number of trucks is enough. According to Shi, the construction of the Huoshenshan hospital will be completed in six days, in which 2,000 containers will be transported from all over the country, as well as prefabricated houses, construction materials, medical supplies and more than 200 lorries will be needed.

Shi-jun receives hundreds of phone calls every day. One night, at one o'clock in the morning, a driver was at a highway junction to pick up the goods. And then sent back to work the next morning, just after 7:00.

Traffic is thin on Wuhan's roads

Busyness

Pingkang is very busy, two or three o'clock in the morning to go to bed has become accustomed to. His wechat group, more than a thousand news day, medical staff constantly seeking help. The messages started at 6 a.m. and continued until one or two in the morning. Some come home from the night shift, some rush to work, some haven't seen their son for a week and want to see.

Drivers make six or seven trips a day, many of them more than a dozen. On January 28, a group of drivers said, "get up in the morning and sneeze, so stay in the house more Huazi, if no problem then go out. ". Some of them live apart from their parents and wives. They have to fight fatigue and take precautions against possible risks. Some people only buy the cheapest mask in the supermarket, go out to wear three layers.

Drivers also receive requests for help from non-medical personnel. Some people mixed in the group, the driver to pick up the location only to find that there is no work card. Some people will directly explain the situation, he is not a medical staff, but the family is sick need car, Pingkang received such a request, but also very helpless, but can only refuse. "We wanted to help them, but we had a rule not to take patients. No matter how pathetic, we couldn't. " The group kept sending out reminders, emphasize only pick up and send medical personnel, medical personnel to provide information to the driver, also ask the driver must verify the identity of passengers. There are professionals who send messages every few hours to remind drivers to take care of personal protection and disinfection.

On the afternoon of January 25, the No. 9 circular issued by the headquarters disrupted the normal working rhythm of the volunteer group.

The notice stated that after 0000 hours on 26 January 2020, the central urban area will be closed to vehicular traffic except for authorized transportation vehicles, free transportation vehicles and official vehicles. On the evening of January 25, it was added that the municipal traffic control department would give 24 hours'notice to drivers of vehicles that were prohibited from passing, and that all vehicles that were not notified would be allowed to pass. In case of emergency, you can pass first and then go to the traffic control department to complete the formalities. Any violation of this notice will be punished severely up to 12 points.

A lot of people don't know whether to go out or not? Health care workers also did not know who would arrange their travel after private cars were also banned. Everyone is in a state of confusion, constantly searching, searching. Early on the morning of January 26th, among the drivers, there were more questions than answers: had anyone been checked out? Is that a penalty? How do you prove it? Can the third ring go up? Is it possible to transport across districts?

People do not know the direction of the policy, some people simply ignore, "points will be deducted, people or to send. Human life is more important. " Some began to wait and see, stopped for a day.

Confusion and uncertainty make drivers even more anxious. They don't know if they will lose their license if they are caught on camera while driving. In an interview with a reporter once deep, a driver very do not understand, he thinks the current measures confusion. "Who would be driving around the city at a time like this if it wasn't necessary for work or a lack of basic necessities? The only people driving outside these days are volunteers, patients' families and medical workers. "

The driver on the road found that the situation can be met with traffic police investigation, explain the situation, take out group chat records, also released, did not say to apply for documents. Someone met the traffic police, was immediately stopped, although at that time let him, but still let him find medical staff or community certification. Some drivers said that they not only did not stop him, but also saluted him when they met the traffic police at the checkpoint.

A volunteer driver was involved in a car accident while transporting supplies

Hidden danger

In recent days, a succession of different volunteer convoys have had some problems.

One driver came home with a fever of 102 on the first day. There's a kid at home, and his wife won't stop crying. Until the fever goes down and the tests confirm it's not the disease, the family can rest assured.

Zhu Wen heard that three other volunteer drivers had also developed fever. He believes that the government should shoulder the responsibility, if necessary, can seek help from the people, and let them do it all the time, is not a long-term solution. "If the government is doing a really good job and doesn't need my help, I'm happier and I don't want to do it. "

And then there were the accidents that started to happen. At 6:10 p.m. on January 26, a driver was involved in an accident while transporting face masks and alcohol. All the bumpers are down, and the right side of the front is badly damaged. Good thing he's okay. The driver said he had to process more than 1,000 messages a minute when he was busy. He worked for 22 hours one day and felt distracted when he was driving.

The driver is also a friend of Ping Kang, the accident first time, he called Ping Kang, looking for someone to pick up the supplies. "He started at around 6 a.m. these days and returned at 11 p.m. , " Ping said. "when he wasn't delivering supplies, he was picking up and dropping off medical staff. I called him one night after 8 p.m. and he told me that he hadn't eaten in a day. "

After what happened, the volunteer corps was thinking, too. They said that the group's initial intention was only to spend the gap, but did not expect the gap time is a bit long.

The founders of the volunteer group were in a quandary.

Drivers from all walks of life, some of the elderly also keep receiving orders, all day in the major hospitals indirect delivery, dinner can not eat, physical energy can not keep up with the overload operation. The administrators of the group are also ad hoc, with an average age and limited experience. Most importantly, there's a lot at stake here, lives are at stake, not a game.

Drivers have suggested that such a fragmented organization must be stopped before it can find a formal public interest organization to anchor it. But it's not easy to stop. At present, there are still many medical staff travel needs can not be addressed, according to nearly four days of statistics, there are 400 medical staff rely on volunteers to provide vehicles to work. If it stops, they don't know what to do with the paramedics.

At one point, when a reporter called the Wuhan Vehicle Emergency Service Hotline and asked about the travel of medical staff, the staff told the reporter that all government-issued vehicles were in the community and needed to be used, and to contact the community to see if they could be dispatched.

On January 24, the new Wuhan Pneumonia Prevention and Control Headquarters issued a notice No. 8, saying that the city urgently collected 6,000 taxis and allocated them to the central city area. Each community 3-5 sets, from the community residents unified dispatch use, from January 25 onwards, for the jurisdiction residents travel free service. But when a paramedic called for help, the response was, "No more cabs. ".

Wuhan Mayor Zhou Xianwang told CCTV's "face to face" on Jan. 27 that the first function of providing 3 to 5 taxis to each community is to take care of the medical staff in the community.

At one time, a reporter called Huaqiao community in Wuhan. The staff said that the community cars were used for the aged and young, and the medical staff had special cars. Tianxing Garden community staff said that if the car has a surplus can be used, no surplus to their own way.

A paramedic left a box of masks behind when he got off the bus

Approach

In a hurry, people get closer to each other.

On the afternoon of the first day of the Lunar New Year, Tsuneyasu went out to buy cat food and picked up two nurses from the Central Hospital, one born in 1995 and the other in 1997. They are anxious, Tsuneyasu said, the hospital masks, protective clothing are not enough, a mask to wear all day, from morning to night can not rest, meals eat instant noodles. The nurses thought about quitting, but they could lose their licenses. At that age, Tsuneyasu said, someone has to be on the front line. After the separation, the two nurses told her to make an appointment to hang out when things were over.

Chen Shun joined the team on the first day of the New Year. The three of them live with their in-laws. "It's not easy for any of us, " Chen said, looking at the medical staff who were coming and going. Chen said that some doctors would issue instructions on how to take precautions in the group, such as wearing multi-layer masks and wearing anti-splash glasses, he would also be reminded to prepare some medical alcohol spray before they got on or off the bus. On the first day of the New Year, a nurse got off the bus and gave him a box of face masks.

A doctor told Chen that they rarely slept, but could only find a place to sleep for half an hour and then go back to work. Some doctors, the child just weaned, the home without milk powder, also dare not put the Child on the side. In the car to call relatives constantly to see if there is a child to drink milk powder can give their children with some.

A nurse, from her home in Wuchang, takes more than an hour to travel. A mother of two, she was staying in a hotel nearby, worried about the impact she was having on her children. Chen Shun said that everyone is a parent, a wife, a husband, he has children, he understands that kind of anxious and helpless.

The old soldier went to pick up the refrigerator once. A girl asked for help on Weibo and Wechat, and her mother died of the illness. Father's been diagnosed, quarantined at the hospital. 20 vials of albumin are in urgent need of refrigeration, and a donation to the refrigerator has been made, but it can not be delivered. Xiang has called the girl. The girl lives in Guanggu, the refrigerator is in Qiaokou District, the father is in Wuhan Ninth Hospital. These three places are over three hours'walk back and forth.

Elephant brother in Hankou, originally intended to directly to the Qiao mouth to pick up the refrigerator and sent to the hospital. The girl wondered if she could come and get her first. She wanted to see her father. Like I promised. Downstairs, her brother came to Florida because he couldn't trust his sister, so he decided to go alone.

Before he got off the bus at the hospital, he left a bag with Rice pudding, buns, a mask and an envelope for brother Xiang. Brother Xiang knows there's money in the envelope. "He brought the fridge up himself and asked me if I could take him back, and I said yes. After he got off, he kept spraying disinfectant, and then he got in the car. "

After dropping him off, Xiangge only left an N95 mask and asked him to take the rest back. He won't go. He won't stop by the CAR. "He asked me how to thank me, and I said, if you want to thank me, go help someone else. That's the kind of thing you say people don't take kindly to, but you've been there, in that situation, and it's very different. "

Later, the little girl to send brother Elephant Wechat, and father's chat records sent over, thank brother elephant saved his father's life. Xiangge recorded a video and sent it to the girl's father: your daughter and son are very good, and when things are over, we will start the new year again.
